commit f22e5565bbf8570135db03a4c3a713ade38c4ec0
Author: Raymond Wagner <rwagner@mythtv.org>
Date:   Wed May 9 01:09:15 2012 -0400

    Fix Recorded.exportMetadata()
    (cherry picked from commit 40243c935e27260dbb280fed353f34dd5d07df35)

commit 7fbcfb4b862069d9caa2c61c811b8602327f6552
Author: Gavin Hurlbut <ghurlbut@mythtv.org>
Date:   Mon May 7 18:09:21 2012 -0700

    Log the Qt version on startup
    (cherry picked from commit 3f6ae11d93577e7ea6ed0b7535ed31834a8837b5)

commit 9e59131ec6d352a6fdafc810b004765ba43588a7
Author: Gavin Hurlbut <ghurlbut@mythtv.org>
Date:   Mon Apr 30 09:43:07 2012 -0700

    Add more debug logs in the DataDirect and MythDLMgr code
    
    Refs #10662
    
    Turns out the problem we are seeing is a known bug in Qt 4.7.1 that is fixed
    in 4.7.2 (and wasn't there before 4.7.1).
    
    In particular, if your Schedules Direct username is an email address, Qt4.7.1
    stupidly puts the username as the part before the @ and the realm as the
    portion after the @, even though the realm was already provided.
    
    SO, if you have a Schedules Direct username that is an email address, either
    upgrade to 4.7.2 (or higher), or downgrade to 4.7.0 (or lower).
    (cherry picked from commit e778f23d0eeabf99be23121cebc190191aa7041f)

commit b9e60ffc62112dd5fb582742b6eb88c4b0f4cdbd
Author: Stuart Morgan <smorgan@mythtv.org>
Date:   Mon May 7 15:22:34 2012 +0100

    Quick fix for a segfault in Playlist::shuffleTracks()
    (cherry picked from commit dc1b2adc40f119ad1ad6c6367b2da01b6e00aacc)

commit 2970fe9d9cd6941335f38c776d97cd02bf6426d5
Author: Jean-Yves Avenard <jyavenard@mythtv.org>
Date:   Sun May 6 15:43:18 2012 +1000

